title: Alexia Bryn
summary: Alexia Marie Bryn (also credited as Schøien and Bryn-Schøien; 24 March 1889 – 19 July 1983) was a Norwegian pair skater. She competed with Yngvar Bryn. They won silver medals at the 1920 Summer Olympics and at the 1923 World Figure Skating Championships, as well as the bronze at the 1912 Worlds.
